library(readxl)

c2015 <- read_xlsx("c2015.xlsx")

c2015.clean <- c2015 %>% 
  drop_na() %>% 
  filter_all(~!(.=='Unknown')) %>% 
  filter_all(~!(.=='Not Rep')) %>% 
  filter_all(~!(.==str_detect(.,'Not Rep'))) %>% 
  filter_all(~!(.==str_detect(.,'Unknown'))) %>% 
  filter_all(~!(.=='Not Reported')) %>% 
  filter(SEAT_POS=='Front Seat, Left Side') %>% 
  mutate(AGE = as.numeric(AGE),
         TRAV_SP = ifelse(TRAV_SP == "Stopped", 0, as.numeric(str_remove(TRAV_SP, "MPH"))))
## Warning in ifelse(TRAV_SP == "Stopped", 0, as.numeric(str_remove(TRAV_SP, :

  1. Refer to this link to have a similar following plot: Horizontal axis is for (monthly) average speed The vertical axis is for months Color by two colors: one for above overall average speed and the other for below the avarage speed The speed on the horizontal axis is standardized
c2015.bar <- c2015.clean %>% 
  group_by(MONTH) %>% 
  summarise(SPEED = mean(TRAV_SP)) %>% 
  mutate(STD_SP = (SPEED - mean(SPEED)) / sd(SPEED),
         FLAG = ifelse(SPEED > mean(SPEED), "Above Average", "Below Average"))

c2015.bar %>% 
  ggplot(aes(reorder(MONTH, STD_SP), STD_SP, fill = FLAG)) + 
  geom_col() +
  labs(x = "Month", y = "Standardized Average Speed",
       title = "Standardized Average Speed by Month") +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_light()

  1. Refer to this link to have a similar following plot: Horizontal Axis is for mean speed Vertical Axis is for INJ_SEV Color by SEX The numbers of speed are shown in points.
c2015.dot <- c2015.clean %>% 
  group_by(INJ_SEV, SEX) %>% 
  summarise(SPEED = round(mean(TRAV_SP), 1)) 

c2015.dot %>% 
  ggplot(aes(reorder(INJ_SEV, SPEED), SPEED, label = SPEED, col = SEX)) + 
  geom_point(size = 10, alpha = 0.7) +
  geom_text(color = "white", size = 2.5) +
  labs(x = "Injury Severity", y = "Average Speed",
       title = "Average Speed by Injury Severity") +
  coord_flip()

  1. Refer to this link to have a similar following plot: Horizontal Axis is for speed Vertical Axis is for DAY Color by SEX The should be a invisible vertical line seperating the two sexes.
c2015.pyramid <- c2015.clean %>% 
  group_by(DAY, SEX) %>% 
  summarise(AVG_SPEED = mean(TRAV_SP)) %>% 
  mutate(AVG_SPEED = ifelse(SEX == "Female", -AVG_SPEED, AVG_SPEED))

c2015.pyramid %>% 
  ggplot(aes(reorder(DAY, -AVG_SPEED), AVG_SPEED, fill = SEX))+
  geom_col() + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = str_c(as.character(c(seq(50, 0, -25), seq(25, 50, 25))))) +
  labs(x = "Day of the Month", y = "Average Speed", title = "Avg. Speed of Males and Females on Each Day of the Month") +
  coord_flip()
